  "prompt": "How do I deal with depression, anxiety and also panic attack?",
  "response": "Here are some strategies to help manage depression, anxiety, and panic attacks:\n\n1. Professional Help\n- Consult a therapist or counselor\n- Consider seeing a psychiatrist for potential medication\n- Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT) can be very effective\n\n2. Mental Health Techniques\n- Practice mindfulness and meditation\n- Deep breathing exercises\n- Progressive muscle relaxation\n- Positive self-talk and affirmations\n\n3. Lifestyle Changes\n- Regular exercise\n- Maintain a consistent sleep schedule\n- Eat a balanced, nutritious diet\n- Limit alcohol and caffeine\n- Reduce stress through time management\n\n4. Coping Strategies for Panic Attacks\n- Learn grounding techniques\n- Use the 5-4-3-2-1 sensory method\n- Recognize and challenge irrational thoughts\n- Create a panic attack response plan\n\n5. Support System\n- Talk to trusted friends and family\n- Join support groups\n- Connect with others experiencing similar challenges\n\n6. Self-Care\n- Set realistic goals\n- Practice self-compassion\n- Engage in activities you enjoy\n- Take breaks when needed\n\n7. Additional Resources\n- Helplines\n- Online mental health resources\n- Mental health apps\n\nRemember, recovery is a process. Be patient and kind to yourself.",
